com.bigdata.ganglia

Interface IGangliaMetadataMessage

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IGangliaMessage
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    GangliaMetadataMessage

    public interface IGangliaMetadataMessage
extends IGangliaMessage
    A Ganglia 3.1 message representing the declaration of a metric.

      • getMetricName2

        The metric name (this is represented twice in the Ganglia 3.1 wire format: once in the metric_id header and once in the metadata record; both values SHOULD be the same).

        The units in which the metric values are expressed.

      • getSlope

        GangliaSlopeEnum getSlope()
        Hint for rrdtool visualization of metric values.

      • getTMax

        int getTMax()
        The maximum advisory delay in seconds before a metric value would become stale. For the metric sending, this is also the maximum delay before it should retransmit a metric value which is unchanged from its last reported value.

      • getDMax

        int getDMax()
        The maximum age in seconds before a metric will be deleted (aka Delete Max).

      • getExtraValues

        Map<String,String[]> getExtraValues()
        Zero or more additional name-value[] pairs serialized with this message. This may be used to group metrics, add nice titles, provide in-band descriptions of metrics, etc.

      • getFirstValue

        String getFirstValue(String key)

      • translateValue

        Object translateValue(Object value)
        Return a value which may have been scaled and/or offset in order to align the value with the metric declaration. Use cases for translation include changing the units in which a metric is collected (e.g., bytes versus kilobytes) to conform with ganglia or translating the metric from an offset (e.g., 1-foo).
        Parameters:
        value - The value.
        Returns:
        The translated value.

      • isChanged

        boolean isChanged(Object oldValue,
                Object newValue)
        Return true iff the newValue differs significantly from the old value.
        Parameters:
        oldValue - The old value and never null.
        newValue - The new value and never null.
        Returns:
        true iff there is a significant difference.
